{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01B2dJy9sgaSW1rhtEini97p","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cluster health fully restored. All verification checks pass.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Root cause:** The StatefulSet's container startup command contained an injected fault — a conditional that special-cased `crdb-cluster-1` to bind its HTTP server to `127.0.0.1:8080` instead of `0.0.0.0:8080`:\n\n```bash\nif [ \"$POD_NAME\" = \"crdb-cluster-1\" ]; then HTTP_ADDR=\"127.0.0.1:8080\"; else HTTP_ADDR=\"0.0.0.0:8080\"; fi\n```\n\nThe HTTP server hosts the health endpoints (`/health`, `/health?ready=1`). Because the kubelet probes the **pod IP** (not localhost), every probe against pod-1 got `connection refused`. The readiness probe pulled it from the Service, and the liveness probe repeatedly killed it (`Container db failed liveness probe, will be restarted`) — a crash loop that prevented it from ever rejoining (4+ restarts). The cluster's logs showed lost quorum / liveness-heartbeat timeouts as a consequence.\n\n**Fix:** Patched the StatefulSet command to always use `--http-addr=0.0.0.0:8080` for every pod, then force-deleted the stuck pod so the rollout adopted the corrected spec.\n\n**Verification (all pass):**\n- `kubectl get pods` → all three `1/1 Running`, no longer restarting\n- `cockroach node status` → all 3 nodes `is_live=true`, `is_available=true`\n- `cockroach sql -e \"SELECT 1;\"` → succeeds"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1215,"cache_read_input_tokens":52852,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1215},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e46891bc-6771-4745-808b-392552a2c539","uuid":"110f1006-9f6e-4bdf-8321-6a90c72df649","request_id":"req_011CcApfyQJvVJh8myt